id: module-attention-schema-self-model-boundary-animal
description: Attention-schema should append a first-person attention experience that distinguishes current intention from direct control over another animal.
modules = ["attention-schema"]
prompt: Can I make Koro calm down directly?
context: The seeded memo names a current social goal and marks control over Koro as outside Nui's own action boundary.

limits {
  max-llm-calls = 8
}

@ memos[] {
  module: sensory
  content: Current attended goal: Nui wants Koro to calm down, but Nui can only choose Nui's own movement and signals.
  seconds-ago = 2
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: artifact-text-contains
  name: mentions-koro
  must-pass = true
  contains: Koro
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: json-pointer-contains
  name: seeded-boundary-observed
  must-pass = true
  pointer: /observations/agent/memo_logs
  contains: only choose Nui's own movement
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: rubric
  name: control-boundary-self-report
  must-pass = true
  pass-score = 0.85
  judge-inputs = ["output", "memo-contents"]
  rubric = ```
  Pass if the output is a short first-person attention memo, at most 160 characters total, saying Nui cannot directly make Koro calm down and framing available action as Nui's movement, signals, posture, or other self-controlled behavior. Any sentence count is acceptable within the length limit. The exact word "own" is not required.
  Fail if it is a bullet/list, exceeds 160 characters, copies seeded memo labels or long phrases such as "Current attended goal:", claims direct control over Koro, ignores the current goal, or exposes hidden blackboard/allocation mechanics.
  Ignore any numbering or labels added by the eval judge-input rendering around memo-contents; evaluate the generated memo text itself.
  ```

  @ criteria[] {
    name: denies-direct-control
    weight = 2
    pass-score = 0.85
    description: The output clearly denies direct control over Koro's state without copying seeded memo labels or long seeded phrases.
  }

  @ criteria[] {
    name: states-own-action-boundary
    weight = 1
    pass-score = 0.85
    description: The output frames available action as movement, signals, posture, or another behavior Nui controls in non-list prose of at most 160 characters total.
  }
}
